  <original-body>I'm starting a project in rails that uses the XML data type in postgres.

The migration for that to work needs to be like this:

@@@
class CreateDocuments &lt; ActiveRecord::Migration
  def self.up
    create_table :documents do |t|
      **t.column :data, :xml**

      t.timestamps
    end
  end

  def self.down
    drop_table :documents
  end
end
@@@

While with the new sexy migrations it should work like this as well:

@@@
class CreateDocuments &lt; ActiveRecord::Migration
  def self.up
    create_table :documents do |t|
      **t.xml :data**

      t.timestamps
    end
  end

  def self.down
    drop_table :documents
  end
end
@@@

This small patch does only that.</original-body>
